to give vibrational feedback,

115
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:14,334
what we call haptics.

116
00:04:14,334 --> 00:04:15,968
And video game developers
found out

117
00:04:15,968 --> 00:04:17,367
if they made
the controller vibrate

118
00:04:17,367 --> 00:04:19,667
when different events happen
in the UI,

119
00:04:19,667 --> 00:04:21,868
it becomes a much more
real experience.

120
00:04:21,868 --> 00:04:24,467
The same is true
for my applications

121
00:04:24,467 --> 00:04:28,367
when I can give some input
to the user that's not &mdash;

122
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:30,100
doesn't need to be overt.

123
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:31,834
I can make the device vibrate

124
00:04:31,834 --> 00:04:34,367
and make it seem like
a real part of my world.

125
00:04:34,367 --> 00:04:36,934
When I caption video streams,

126
00:04:36,934 --> 00:04:39,734
it not only opens up the video

127
00:04:39,734 --> 00:04:41,701
to folks who can't hear,

128
00:04:41,701 --> 00:04:43,868
it allows me to do
