00:05:43,834 --> 00:05:46,133
Rosenthal: So let's talk
a little bit about the users,

153
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:48,968
people who use
accessible technology.

154
00:05:48,968 --> 00:05:51,100
It's really important
for you to understand them

155
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:54,000
and how they interact
with your products,

156
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
just like all your other
users, right?

157
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,534
So the main thing
to keep in mind

158
00:05:57,534 --> 00:05:59,701
are the input and output
technologies that they use

159
00:05:59,701 --> 00:06:02,367
and making sure that you have
multiple redundant ways

160
00:06:02,367 --> 00:06:04,067
of interacting
with your applications &mdash;

161
00:06:04,067 --> 00:06:06,234
basically not relying
on a mouse,

162
00:06:06,234 --> 00:06:07,734
not relying on rollovers

163
00:06:07,734 --> 00:06:09,033
to be able to get
to your content.

164
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:11,133
So main ones to keep in mind

165
00:06:11,133 --> 00:06:14,200
are for input using
keyboard and voice and touch,

166
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,100
and then some special
purpose displays

167
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:18,400
like this Braille display
that we have pictured here

168
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,033
where you can do corded input.

169
00:06:20,033 --> 00:06:21,634
And then also for feedback &mdash;

170
00:06:21,634 --> 00:06:23,400
feedback's really vital
so that your user knows

171
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,734
where they are on the screen

172
00:06:24,734 --> 00:06:26,000
and what
they're interacting with

173
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,868
at all points in time, right?

174
00:06:27,868 --> 00:06:29,467
So you should
make sure to have, again,

175
00:06:29,467 --> 00:06:30,868
redundant feedback as well.

176
00:06:30,868 --> 00:06:33,567
So not only have speech
but other audio cues

177
00:06:33,567 --> 00:06:38,100
for when tasks complete or other
notifications are happening,

178
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:39,767
and also vibration feedback,

179
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:41,434
so that you get
that sense of reality

180
00:06:41,434 --> 00:06:43,000
when you're using the product.

181
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,934
Plus, keep in mind other things
like the Braille display

182
00:06:44,934 --> 00:06:46,634
that we have here
as another input &mdash;

183
00:06:46,634 --> 00:06:50,267
or output device,
in this case.

184
00:06:50,267 --> 00:06:52,634
Green: Okay. So we've got
a list of a couple things,

